body:
No, I don't want that behavior. If someone accidentally cancels the decompression in the middle, they have no way to recover cleanly.
If you don't want to re-decompress, simply don't rerun this frame.
Note that the situation is different for the download since we want to avoid DDOSing the server hosting the data, and we have a check for the integrity of the downloaded file to warn if the file is only half downloaded.
